description.narrative: With strong advocacy and technical support, UNICEF secured top-level political commitment to address VAC through the National Plan of Action for Children 2021-2030, with a component on child protection system strengthening. Other programmes adopted in 2021 include the National Programme on Social Work Development 2021-2030, the National Programme on Child Labour Prevention and Elimination 2021-2025, and the National Programme on Child Online Protection 2021-2025. The issuance of appropriate measures on protection of children and women in COVID-19 provided better care and protection of children and women in quarantine, child victims of abuse, orphans, child labourers and other vulnerable children. | Status:Met | As-of Date:03/02/2022
